<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Power Cylinders - Installation -
        Assembling Piston and Connecting Rod Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="4">
        <title>Assembling Piston and Connecting Rod Assembly</title>
        <figure id="f26508install02" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH04/H04009.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing piston rings (466 piston shown)</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure that the top side of both compression rings (marked with a dot) are facing up. The oil
                    control ring may be installed with either side facing up, if new.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_175.xml" xrefid="t08007" appearance="hottext">piston ring expander tool
                </hotlnk>
                to install the piston rings. Install the oil control ring first, then intermediate compression ring, and
                finally the top compression ring.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid engine damage, orientation of a reused piston skirt is very important due to wear
                    patterns. Install the skirt on the crown using the original skirt orientation.
                </para>
            </caution>
            <note>
                <para>New piston skirts may be oriented in either direction due to piston skirt symmetry.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f26508install01" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH04/H04012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing piston skirt on crown (570 engine only)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Skirt</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Crown</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">
                <emph type="bold">For 570 engines only:</emph>
                Install the piston skirt on the crown. Make sure that the oil jet cutouts on the skirt are facing away
                from the crown.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the piston pin bore with clean engine oil.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f26508install03" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH04/H04014.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing the piston pin</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Align the bores in the connecting rod and piston and install the piston pin.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury or possible death, wear safety glasses when installing retaining
                    rings.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f26508install04" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH04/H04005.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Installing piston pin retaining rings</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use pliers to install the piston pin retaining rings.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
